rComments: He is very passionate about the environment and the Arctic, but he is not good at teaching. He definitely knows what he is talking about but he often goes on tangents that are not actually related to the lecture. And those tangents end up on the midterms. It is an interesting class but I don't recommend taking it with him!

Paul is super monotone, his 8:30 classes are brutal. Exams aren't too bad however, they're mostly multiple choices. Would recommend a different teacher,  not to mention he rides a Scooter to class....

Paul is super monotone during his lectures, so the 8:30s are hard to deal with, but I found myself coming to class solely because what we discussed was super interesting. He has a tendency to go off on tangents, and not be able to get back to what he was originally talking about. However, he's very passionate about his field of study

If you are interested in a professor who cannot articulate coherent points, or give accurate information about topics that are not covered on readings, you will not enjoy this course. The professor is smart, but is a terrible prof. You can easily get a 9.0 if you read the online material and never go to class. Believe me, at 8:30, his class is bad.

This professor made me hate my life. Class was so long and boring. There were so many exercises and work, like so many and it was so annoying because they were long busy work. Textbook for the class was so expensive. Never going to take this professors classes again, avoid like the plague.

AMAZING MAN. Always gives you extra chances to succeed (extra credit, bonus marks etc). Super smart and really passionate about what he teaches. He's an inspiration to us all and is the most genuine and approachable prof I've had at UOttawa. TAKE ANY CLASS YOU CAN WITH HIM. He's a sweetheart. Can't say enough good things about him. Love you Paul!

This prof is amazing! He teaches really interesting content and gives students really easy ways to earn marks. He'll work with you if an assignment or midterm doesn't fit your school schedule. After taking 2 courses with him (GEG 3300 AND GEG 3321), I'm super happy with both my grades from him. Really funny too!
best teacher ever. Was there 4 me when i wuz down and helped me with al my problems.  Highly Recommend   Hard marker tho
Smart and passionate. Uses a lot of online material, somewhat sporadically... So keep up with what he posts on Blackboard.

Very Nice guy. But it seamed as if he was reading straight from the book.  He's also very fair with the marking.  Half of the questions on his final exam consisted of questions from the first and second midterm and he hinted what the bonus question would be.  People should realize this is a Science course not an arts course.

Professor Beckwith was such a great professor, always there for us. He was so funny and inspirational at times, which made me look forward to class. The tests were challenging, but I felt the class had a very positive effect on me. It's really too bad that he does not teach many more classes otherwise I would be in them! Recommended for sure.
Awesome, I learned so much. Very important topic that everybody should know.
Good prof, a bit of a hard marker, but I learned a lot of interesting things in his climatology class!

He enjoys rambling off on tangents, and sometimes loses his train of thought mid-sentence, but sometimes those tangents will show up in the tests, so pay attention. If you make good lecture notes and attend class you should be fine. Also, he gives bonus questions on the tests, so if you don't know absolutely everything, don't sweat it.

As a PHD candidate at uOttawa with an engineering and physics background, this professor has a passionate stance on human induced climate change. His strong opinions on the subject bleeds into his teachings and he tends to ramble out of no where for around 30 minutes mid lecture. This course had easy but very long labs,  the exams were fair though.

on dieu quel esti d bon prof! Je vous encourage fortement de prendre ce cours! Auparavant, j'ai détesté la recherche, mais à cause de lui et sa motivation la recherche n'est plus une notion qui fait peur. Il fait rire, en plus il comprends très bien ses étudiants, soit anglophone ou francophone. Très hot en passant!
Awesome prof, best I have had...
